  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: 1.6.5\r\nOS & Version: Windows 10 64-bit\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\n\r\nLight mode syncs, ethminer connects and gets to work\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\n\r\nLight mode syncs just fine, but ethminer claims that the eth_submitHashrate does not exist/is not available\r\n\r\nSpecifically: \r\n\r\n~~~~C:\\Users\\Your Mom>B:\\Downloads\\ethminer-0.9.41-genoil-1.0.5-cuda6.5\\ethminer.exe -U > log.txt\r\nminer  08:56:28|main  Getting work package...\r\n  X  08:56:28|main  Failed to submit hashrate.\r\n  X  08:56:28|main  Dynamic exception type: class jsonrpc::JsonRpcException\r\nstd::exception::what: Exception -32601 : METHOD_NOT_FOUND: The method being requested is not available on this server: The method eth_submitHashrate does not exist/is not available\r\n\r\nJSON-RPC problem. Probably couldn't connect. Retrying in 1...\r\nminer  08:56:30|main  Getting work package...\r\n  X  08:56:30|main  Failed to submit hashrate.\r\n  X  08:56:30|main  Dynamic exception type: class jsonrpc::JsonRpcException\r\nstd::exception::what: Exception -32601 : METHOD_NOT_FOUND: The method being requested is not available on this server: The method eth_submitHashrate does not exist/is not available\r\n~~~~\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\n\r\nHappens with any --light compatible version of geth and any version of ethminer, tested on 1.0.x and above",
