    "created_at": "2017-06-12T09:23:40Z",
    "updated_at": "2017-06-12T09:23:40Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "A light client does not have the chain's state available locally, rather tries to request it on demand. This means however that mining is pointless, because every transaction you want to process would need to wait arbitrarily long to execute until the client downloads all the needed data to run it.\r\n\r\nIf you wish to mine, please run a full node (or use a mining pool if you do now wish to run your own node).",
